  <refnamediv>
    <refname>immeanstddev</refname>
    <refpurpose>Compute per-channel image mean and standard deviation.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   [meanValue, stdValue] = immeanstddev(im)
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>im</term><listitem><para>Input image or numeric array.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>meanValue</term><listitem><para>Mean value. Multichannel inputs return one value per channel.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>stdValue</term><listitem><para>Standard deviation value. Multichannel inputs return one value per channel.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>

<refsection role="arguments">
   <title>Arguments</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry><term>im :</term><listitem><para>Input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
        <varlistentry><term>meanValue :</term><listitem><para>Row vector of per-channel mean values.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
        <varlistentry><term>stdValue :</term><listitem><para>Row vector of per-channel population standard deviations.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
      <function>immeanstddev</function> computes per-channel statistics in the same style as OpenCV <function>meanStdDev</function>.
   </para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
im = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/" + "baboon.png"));
[m, s] = immeanstddev(im);
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

